WORLDWIDE  INFORMATION INFRASTRUCTURE

Detailed information on the information infrastructures of countries 
throughout the world are contained in a just-released report, WORLD 
TELECOMMUNICATION DEVELOPMENT REPORT:  INFORMATION INFRASTRUCTURES.
 
The report contains 150 pages of detailed textual information plus 
100 pages of statistical tables.  It costs 100 Swiss francs from the 
International Telecommunications Union, Sales and Marketing Service, 
Place des Nations, 1211 Geneva 20, Switzerland; phone 011-41-22-730-
5111; fax 011-41-22-733-7256.



