January 1, 1996

Speculators buy bankrupt Hyogo Bank shares on TSE+

TOKYO, Dec. 25 Kyodo

     The bankrupt Hyogo Bank topped the list of most active stocks
on the Tokyo Stock Exchange on Monday as speculators engaged in a
heavy ''money game,'' traders said.
     They said an estimated 12.8 million shares were traded despite
the bank's delisting, set for Jan. 29 next year, boosting the price
of its stock to 2.00 yen per share, double its Friday closing of 1.00
yen.
     Hyogo Bank's operations will be transferred to newly inaugurated
Midori Bank early next year.



