January 1, 1996

Shinozawa vows to tighten surveillance system+

TOKYO, Dec. 28 Kyodo

     Vice Finance Minister Kyosuke Shinozawa said Thursday the
ministry will proceed with a proposed reform of its inspection and
surveillance system in a bid to prevent illicit financial operations
like the Daiwa Bank scandal.
     ''The Daiwa Bank case taught the ministry a lesson and it will
do its utmost to flesh out measures proposed to make its banking
policy more transparent,'' Shinozawa said at a press conference.
     His comment came after a former manager of the New York branch
of Daiwa Bank was indicted by a federal grand jury Wednesday on
